{
  "message": "feat(newproj): improve tech stack display and add wizard recording\n\n## UI Enhancement: Tech Stack Display\n\nThe tech stack selection screen now displays human-readable labels for\nauto-detected technologies instead of raw internal identifiers.\n\nBefore: \"Auto-detected: node\"\nAfter:  \"Auto-detected: Node.js / JavaScript / TypeScript\"\n\nChanges to screen_tech_stack.sh:\n- Added loop to convert detected tech identifiers to display labels\n- Uses get_tech_option_display() to fetch human-readable names\n- Builds comma-separated list of detected technologies\n- Improves user experience by showing meaningful technology names\n\n## Documentation: Asciinema Recording\n\nAdded complete TUI wizard flow recording (docs/newproj_tui.cast) that\ndemonstrates the full project creation experience:\n\n1. Welcome screen with ACFS branding\n2. Project name input with validation rules\n3. Directory selection with default path\n4. Tech stack selection with auto-detection\n5. Feature selection (beads, Claude Code, AGENTS.md, UBS)\n6. AGENTS.md preview with sections list\n7. Review & confirm with file tree preview\n8. Progress screen with step-by-step creation\n9. Success screen with next steps\n\nThe recording can be played with: asciinema play docs/newproj_tui.cast\n\nThis supports the newproj TUI screenshot/recording task (agentic_coding_flywheel_setup-aiwf).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
